# Testing Standards

## Test Organization
The project includes comprehensive testing in [tests/](mdc:tests/):

- [tests/test_runner.zig](mdc:tests/test_runner.zig) - Main test runner
- [tests/test_database.zig](mdc:tests/test_database.zig) - Database functionality tests
- [tests/test_simd_vector.zig](mdc:tests/test_simd_vector.zig) - SIMD operations tests
- [tests/test_performance_*.zig](mdc:tests/test_performance_*.zig) - Performance regression tests

## Testing Categories

### Unit Tests
- Test individual functions and modules
- Use `std.testing` for assertions
- Include edge cases and error conditions
- Test both success and failure paths

### Integration Tests
- Test cross-module functionality
- Verify API compatibility
- Test end-to-end workflows
- Include real-world usage scenarios

### Performance Tests
- Benchmark critical operations
- Detect performance regressions
- Compare against baseline metrics
- Test with various data sizes

### Memory Tests
- Verify proper memory management
- Detect memory leaks
- Test allocation patterns
- Verify cleanup procedures

## Test Structure
```zig
test "descriptive test name" {
    const allocator = testing.allocator;
    
    // Setup
    var obj = try Object.init(allocator);
    defer obj.deinit();
    
    // Test
    const result = try obj.operation();
    try testing.expect(result == expected);
    
    // Cleanup (handled by defer)
}
```

## Testing Best Practices
- Use descriptive test names that explain what is being tested
- Include setup and cleanup in each test
- Use `testing.allocator` for memory allocations
- Test error conditions and edge cases
- Verify resource cleanup with `defer` statements

## Performance Testing
- Use [benchmarks/](mdc:benchmarks/) for performance benchmarks
- Include warmup iterations before timing
- Test with various data sizes and configurations
- Compare against established performance targets

## Test Coverage
- Aim for 95%+ test coverage
- Test all public APIs
- Include error handling tests
- Test concurrent operations
- Verify memory safety

## Running Tests
- Use `zig build test` for standard tests
- Use `zig test` for individual test files
- Use `zig build benchmark` for performance tests
- Include tests in CI/CD pipeline

## Test Data
- Use realistic test data when possible
- Include edge cases (empty inputs, large inputs, etc.)
- Test with various vector dimensions
- Include both valid and invalid inputs